To determine if 2111159 is a prime number, we need to check if it has any divisors other than 1 and itself. A common approach is to test divisibility by all prime numbers up to the square root of the number. However, for large numbers like 2111159, this can be computationally intensive without specialized tools.

For simplicity and accuracy, we can use a function that checks for primality. Here’s how you can do it:

```php
<?php
function isPrime($number) {
    if ($number <= 1) return false;
    if ($number == 2 || $number == 3) return true;
    if ($number % 2 == 0 || $number % 3 == 0) return false;

    // Check divisibility by all integers up to the square root of the number
    for ($i = 5; $i * $i <= $number; $i += 6) {
        if ($number % $i == 0 || $number % ($i + 2) == 0) return false;
    }
    return true;
}

$number = 2111159;
if (isPrime($number)) {
    echo "$number is a prime number.";
} else {
    echo "$number is not a prime number.";
}
?>
